<HEADLINE> Mowlam Denies Bill Will Legalize IRA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Northern Ireland Secretary Mo Mowlam
denied Saturday that she was planning to make the Irish Republican
Army (IRA) a legal organization.
</P>
<P>
She said new legislation on prisoner releases simply provided a
means for specifying organizations whose members will not benefit
from early releases.
</P>
<P>
Daily Mail reported Saturday that the Northern Ireland
Secretary will have the power to end the organization's terrorist
status under legislation authorizing the release of paramilitary
prisoners.
</P>
<P>
Mowlam said: "The reports are absolutely untrue." Those talking
about plans to de-proscribe the IRA were unhelpfully trying to
confuse the public, she added.
</P>
<P>
She insisted the Bill contained rigorous safeguards. Those
prisoners still judged a danger to public safety would not be let
out and those who re-offended would be returned to prison.  
</P>
</TEXT>
