<HEADLINE> Angolan Minister Off to Attend UN Anti-Drug </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, June 6 (Xinhua) -- A delegation led by Angolan Justice
Minister Paulo Chipilica left here Saturday for the United
Nations to attend the World Anti-Drug Conference scheduled for
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The minister told the press before his departure that the
conference is very important to all countries in the world, since
drug addiction and smuggling has turned into a worldwide
disaster, plaguing the mankind, especially the youth.
</P>
<P>
He said he will appeal to the international community to help
eliminate competely drug-trafficking through Angolan territories.
</P>
<P>
Due to instability as a result of the war, Angola is incapable
of preventing drugs from entering the country effectively,
Chipilica noted, adding that drug smugglers transport drugs via
the Angolan territories before reaching Europe through regions
like Latin America.
</P>
<P>
He pledged that his government will make more efforts in
fighting drug addiction and smuggling after peace is finally
achieved in Angola. 
</P>
</TEXT>
