<HEADLINE> Russia Concerned over Conflict between Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Russia stated Saturday that it was
deeply concerned over the outbreak of hostilities between Ethiopia
and Eritrea, and called on the two African states to halt their
bombing raids.
</P>
<P>
Eritrea and Ethiopia unleashed warplanes on bombing raids
against each other Friday, shattering hopes that a peace formula
to quell their border war had been found.
</P>
<P>
The Russian Foreign Ministry said in a statement that "These
acts essentially raise the armed stand-off between the two
countries to a new and considerable more dangerous level."
</P>
<P>
The ministry once again "appeals to the opposing sides to show
sense, stop their military actions and sit down immediately at the
negotiating table."
</P>
<P>
According to the Russian Foreign Ministry, the United Nations
has begun evacuating foreigners from Eritrea by plane. Ethiopia,
which at first refused to allow the plane to fly over its
territory to evacuate foreigners from Eritrea, granted permission
to enter its airspace from 6 p.m. (1400 GMT) to 8 p.m. (1600 GMT).
</P>
