<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Tanzanian President Benjamin
Mkapa Saturday dissolved the newly launched Parole National and
Regional Boards.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued here, the president orders the Minister
of Home Affairs to renominate the board members so as to give
equal chances to people from different communities.
</P>
<P>
The Parole National and Regional Boards, comprising 40 members
from different regions in the country, was launched Monday by the
Prime Minister Frederick Sumaye.
</P>
<P>
After the establishment of the organization, a lot of people
complained about the nomination of the members and called for its
dissolvement. They said the body comprises many people with
religious backgrounds who might be biased.
</P>
<P>
The parole system was aimed at reducing crimes in the country
and easing congestions in prisons. 
