<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's Composite Consumer Price
Index went up 1.5 percent in March to 2990.6, compared with
2,946.4 in February, the Nigerian TV Authority (NTA) reported
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted figures released by the Federal Office of
Statistics (FOS) as saying that the country's inflation rate
dropped from 7.7 percent in February to seven percent in March.
</P>
<P>
The Composite Consumer Price Index is a measurement of the
changes in the average retail prices of food items, consumer
goods and services in both urban and rural Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
The FOS said increase in the consumer price level is mainly a
result of higher prices in food items, fuel and transport.
