<HEADLINE> Tanzania to Check Quality of Cosmetics in Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 6 (Xinhua) -- The Tanzania Bureau of
Standards (TBS) will examine cosmetic products in the market to
prevent their harm to consumers, especially women.
</P>
<P>
TBS acting director Beatrice Mutabazi said most cosmetics in
the country's market are unsafe, reports said here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"Foreign countries are dumping unsafe cosmetic products to
Tanzania and it is necessary to inspect the quality of the
cosmetics which are used by most Tanzanian women," Mutabazi was
quoted as saying Friday.
</P>
<P>
The bureau has appealed to the Ministry of Industries and
Trade to promulgate import regulations on the standard and
quality of cosmetics, she said.
</P>
<P>
She revealed that the regulations are being drafted and once
they are officially announced, TBS will direct all cosmetic
importers to strictly adhere to the regulations.
</P>
<P>
The regulations will require all imported goods to comply with
the standards of Tanzania or the manufacturing country. In
addition, the exporting country will have to certify that the
product is safe and used both at home and abroad, the official
said.
</P>
<P>
Mutabazi said that TBS will enter into bilateral agreements
with the quality supervision authorities of the exporting country
to ensure that the cosmetics have been certified before they are
imported to Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
The acting director has advised people to buy cosmetics from
pharmacies instead of street kiosks and shops. 
</P>
</TEXT>
