<HEADLINE> Forest Fire-Prevention Warning Sent Out </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Chinese forestry authorities have
issued an emergency notice calling for heightened alert for
possible forest fires.
</P>
<P>
The notice followed a recent rash of forest fires in the
country. The notice urged an immediate, thorough investigation of
fire-prevention measures.
</P>
<P>
It called on forest fire-prevention offices at all levels to
strengthen forecasting, adhere to 24-hour patrols, and tighten fire
reporting.
</P>
<P>
The notice requires leadership at all levels to take the lead
in strengthening prevention measures and improving related
publicity.
</P>
<P>
Strict precautions must be taken against making unauthorized
open-air fires in forest areas, officials said.  
