<DOCNO> XIE19980607.0032 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Collection of Foreigners' Testimony on Nanjing Massacre Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, June 7 (Xinhua) -- A collection of testimony by
foreigners on the Nanjing Massacre by Japanese troops in 1937 has
been published by the Jiangsu People's Publishing House.
</P>
<P>
The book, in 320,000 Chinese characters, includes on-the-spot
reports on the event, diaries and letters, news coverage,
recollections and autobiographies written by more than 40
foreigners from Britain, the United States, Germany and Japan who
were in Nanjing during the event.
</P>
<P>
Also included in the book are archival materials published by
the United States, Germany and Japan, the testimony of foreigners
at the Far East International Military Tribunal in Tokyo and
China's Military Tribunal to try war criminals and confessions of
Japanese military officers and soldiers.
</P>
<P>
On December 13, 1937, Japanese intruding troops seized the city
of Nanjing and massacred a reported 300,000 innocent Chinese
civilians and unarmed soldiers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
