<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1500 GMT, June 7 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- Pakistani Information Minister Mushahid Hussain
Sunday strongly condemned India for fomenting state terrorism via
its intelligence outfit while expressing regret for the loss of
life in the train bomb blast early in the morning.
</P>
<P>
Mushahid said in a statement Sunday evening that the government
had evidence of the involvement of India's Research and Analysis
Wing (RAW) in the current series of terroristic acts, which first
targeted a cinema in Lahore and now a train through a time-bomb.
(BC-Pakistan-India-Terrorism)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NICOSIA -- European Union (EU) Task Force chief Nikolaus van
der Pas has appealed to the Turkish Cypriots for their joining the
Cypriot government controlled by Greek Cypriots in the EU
accession talks.
</P>
<P>
Van der Pas, director general of the European Commission's Task
Force for accession negotiations, made the call at the end of his
three-day fact-finding mission here, which is part of Cyprus'
accession process. (BC-Cyprus-EU)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- Pakistan Sunday accused the Indian intelligence
agency of masterminding the train bomb blast in southern
Pakistan, killing 23 and injuring more than 30.
</P>
<P>
The bomb blast in the train Khyber Mail "is obviously an
abominable terrorist act sponsored by (India's) Research and
Analysis Wing (RAW)," the Pakistani Foreign Office said Sunday
afternoon in a written statement. (BC-Pakistan-Blast-India)
</P>
<P>
