SEOUL -- South Korea's navy may resume its destroyer-building
program later this year, said the Defense Ministry Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Seeking to secure funds needed for the resumption of the
program named KDX-2, the Ministry draws up a revision to the
supplementary budget, which will be submitted to the National
Assembly in September for approval.
(BC-SKorea-Destroyers-Building) 
