<HEADLINE> OAU Deeply Concerned Over Crisis in Comoros </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OUAGADOUGOU, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The Organization of African
Unity (OAU) has expressed deep concern over the unrelenting
crisis and the negative attitude of the Anjouan separatists
toward peace in the Comoros.
</P>
<P>
"The Anjouan separatists have deliberately blocked all
attempts at finding a peaceful and negotiated solution based on
the legitimate aspiration of the population and the cardinal
principle of the unity and territorial integrity of the Comoros,"
said a resolution adopted by an OAU council of ministers meeting
to end here Sunday night.
</P>
<P>
The four-day 68th ordinary session of OAU council of ministers
strongly condemned the unworthy treatment meted out by the
Anjouan separatists to the members of the OAU ministerial
delegation during the visit to the Anjouan island last March.
</P>
<P>
The ministers met with threats and open acts of hostility from
the separatists on their peace mission.
</P>
<P>
The action of the separatists represented a serious threat to
peace, security and stability in the Comoros and the countries in
the Indian Ocean region in general, the resolution says.
</P>
<P>
This also "constituted a very dangerous precedent which could
serve as an example elsewhere in Africa and flouts one of the
most fundamental principles of the OAU, the respect of which is
major for the maintenance of peace, security and stability in
Africa," the resolution points out.
</P>
<P>
The meeting endorsed the recommendations made by the
ministerial delegation at the end of its visit to the Comorian
Archipelago, requesting the countries in the region to take every
necessary step to ensure the respect of principle of unity and
territorial integrity of the Comoros.
</P>
<P>
OAU member states were urgently called upon to aid the
countries in the region and the Comorian government in ending the
current situation and open the new way for a lasting solution to
the crisis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
