<HEADLINE> Exchanges on Culture of Chinese Nation to be Expanded </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The second executive council
meeting of the Society for the Culture of the Chinese Nation,
which closed here today, called for more cultural exchanges
between domestic and overseas scholars.
</P>
<P>
The society will work together with the Chinese University of
Hong Kong to hold an international seminar on Chinese culture and
the 21st century this winter, the conference decided.
</P>
<P>
With the seminar leading the central topic, a number of
academic activities will also be held. Special works and
audio-video materials are expected to be collected and compiled,
and awards will be given to the authors who write good papers on
the topic.
</P>
<P>
At the conference today, Xiao Ke was elected first president of
the society; Fei Xiaotong and Cheng Siyuan were elected
presidents. Another 30 people -- including Zhuang Yanlin, Hei Boli
and Li Baoguang -- were elected vice-presidents.
</P>
<P>
Set up in 1990, the non-governmental society is aimed at
expanding the Chinese culture and contributing to the country's
modernization drive and the great cause of the motherland's
reunification.  
</P>
</TEXT>
