<HEADLINE> Environmental Sector Opts for Foreign Investment in Shaanxi Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, June 7 (Xinhua) -- A new policy encouraging more
overseas investment in the environmental protection industry has
been formulated and promulgated in northwest China's Shaanxi
Province.
</P>
<P>
According to the new policy, Shaanxi plans to introduce large
amounts of advanced environmental protection facilities within the
coming years and welcome foreign businesses to directly invest or
participate in the restructuring of state-owned environmental
protection enterprises.
</P>
<P>
And foreign businesses who take part in the restructuring of
medium- and small-size state-enterprises will receive the same
preferential policies for the province's non-state-owned
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Enterprises that utilize waste water, waste gas or waste residue
as production materials are entitled to tax reductions within a
five-year period, according to the policy.
</P>
<P>
The environmental protection sector, presently the pillar
industry of Shaanxi Province, is expected to maintain an annual
growth rate of 25 percent, said a senior official with the
provincial government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
