<HEADLINE> OAU Calls for Int'l Aid to S. Leone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OUAGADOUGOU, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The Organization of African
Unity (OAU) has called for immediate and generous humanitarian
assistance to the people of Sierra Leone, beset with continuous
civil war, especially after last year's military coup.
</P>
<P>
In a resolution adopted by an OAU Council of Ministers meeting
to end here Sunday night, the continental organization appealed
to the international community, OAU members in particular, to
give the Sierra Leonean government all possible assistance in its
efforts to rehabilitate and reconstruct the west African country.
</P>
<P>
The elected government in that country was restored in March
after the west African peace keeping force known as ECOMOG drove
out the military junta which seized power in a coup in May last
year.
</P>
<P>
Welcoming the return of the government of President Ahmed
Tejan Kabbah, the 68th Ordinary Session of OAU Council of
Ministers also urged the United Nations and the international
community to help meet the logistical and technical requirements
of ECOMOG, which has been mandated by President Kabbah to take
care of security affairs of the country.
</P>
<P>
Enough support should be given by the international community
in the disarmament and demobilization of armed personnel in that
country so as to ensure general security.
</P>
<P>
The Council of Ministers also called upon the remaining forces
of the ousted junta and allied rebels to cease the atrocities
they have been committing in the northern and eastern parts of
Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
The ministers agreed that a process of national reconciliation
between Kabbah's government and various groups concerned should
be encouraged. 
</P>
