<HEADLINE> First Chinese University Passes ISO9001 Quality Test </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Three authoritative Norwegian
maritime experts have approved the quality authentication of
China's leading shipping university.
</P>
<P>
Dalian Maritime University, located in northeast China's
Liaoning Province, is the first university in the country to pass
the ISO9001 authentication.
</P>
<P>
"The introduction of ISO9001 into Chinese universities is
conducive to modern higher education in the country," said
Prof. Si Yuzhuo, president of Dalian university, here Saturday
evening.
</P>
<P>
The International Convention on Standards of Training,
Certification and Watch-keeping for Seafarers (STCWS), which China
joined in 1984, regulates the higher-education and training
institutions on maritime affairs to establish an educational
quality-guarantee system.
</P>
<P>
Green seamen and cadets in shipping schools are required to
receive special training in compliance with the STCWS since August
1 this year.
</P>
<P>
The three Norwegian experts from the DNV, a prestigious
shipping society in Norway, unanimously agreed on the ISO9001
authentication for the university's shipping college, turbine
engineering college, adult education colleges, shipping training
and research center, and foreign languages department.
</P>
<P>
The university, under the Chinese Ministry of Communications,
covers all fields of maritime affairs. It has a current enrollment
of 6,500 students, including those for their doctoral and master's
degrees.  
</P>
</TEXT>
