<HEADLINE> Medical Diagnosis Conducted in Anhui Province Via Internet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Doctors in Hefei, capital city of
east China's Anhui Province, and Shanghai Municipality have
performed an experimental long-distance medical diagnosis on a
patient in Wuhu city through the "169" public multi-media
communication network.
</P>
<P>
Dialing the 169 network, all three sides can link their
long-distance medical working stations to a central service
terminal in Hefei, capital of Anhui.
</P>
<P>
After processing in the central terminal, pictures and sound
are available to each side. Each can also see X-rays and CT
photographs, medical records, pathological reports and diagnostic
conclusions.
</P>
<P>
This is the first reported case in China of a long-distance
medical diagnosis through the Internet.  
</P>
</TEXT>
