<HEADLINE> Ancient Tombs Discovered in Hebei Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Archeologists have discovered
a group of ancient tombs of the Tang Dynasty (618-907) in northern
Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
Unearthed so far from the nine tombs in Liyuan Village, Anguo
City are more than 40 pieces of cultural relics like pottery
figures and handicrafts in the shape of various animals in
addition to copper coins and decorations.
</P>
<P>
Pottery figures dressed in the costumes of ethnic minority
people and Europeans hold special appeal for archeologists, who
say these relics are important in the study of culture, economy
and external cultural exchange during the Tang Dynasty. 
