<HEADLINE> Police Officers Punished for Corruption in Hainan Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, June 7 (Xinhua) -- A total of 76 police officers have
been punished in China's southernmost Hainan Province because of a
province-wide anti-corruption campaign which brought to light
their illicit activities.
</P>
<P>
Among the 76 officers, involving 68 cases uncovereed in
violation of laws or disciplines between January and May this
year, 13 have been transferred to the procuratorial organs; 63
given disciplinary action; and 23 members been dispelled from the
provincial police force because of serious nature of their cases.
</P>
<P>
Liu Leping, deputy director of the Municipal Public Security
Bureau of Qionghai City, Hainan, as well as two other police
officers, were convicted of perjury in a homicide case.
</P>
<P>
In another case, a criminal police officer surnamed Lin in
Haikou, capital city of the island province, reportedly
misappropriated 620,000 yuan (747,000 US dollars) of public funds
and then took flight. Lin was seized soon after his flight.
</P>
