<HEADLINE> Fund for Risk Investment in High-tech to be Established </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, June 7 (Xinhua) -- China will establish a special fund
for risk investment in high technology around the end of the year,
according to financial specialists attending a forum today on the
development strategy of China's capital market in the port city of
Qingdao.
</P>
<P>
Sources at the forum in east China's Shandong Province said
that the People's Bank of China (PBC), the China Securities
Regulatory Commission and the Ministry of Finance are framing a
mechanism for such risk investment, and the mechanism is expected
to boost the country's high-tech industry.
</P>
<P>
Since the high-tech industry is considered high risk with high
returns, commercial banks which have a highly floating pattern of
liabilities cannot fund some high-tech projects. Therefore, a
mechanism of risk investment in high technology on the basis of a
sound capital market is essential, according to the specialists.
</P>
</TEXT>
