<HEADLINE> EU to Fund China's Biggest Environmental Protection Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) has
decided to invest 37 million European dollars in China's biggest
environmental protection project in northeast China's Liaoning
Province.
</P>
<P>
Endymion Wilkinson, EU Ambassador on an investigation trip
here, said in an interview with Xinhua that the EU-funded project
is expected to be launched after the EU-Chinese contract is
formally signed on Tuesday during the Chinese Minister of Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation Shi Guangsheng's trip to European
Union countries.
</P>
<P>
The five-year project will cover seven sub-projects including
urban development planning for Liaoning's provincial capital of
Shenyang; the administration of water, energy resources and air
quality; and the adjustment of industrial structures.
</P>
<P>
Wilkinson said the EU expects this to become a demonstration
project in China.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning Province has collected 11.5 million European dollars
to launch the EU-funded project.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning is an old industrial base with increasing pollution
problems.
</P>
<P>
An EU consulting company will start its work for the project in
Liaoning this September. 
</P>
</TEXT>
