<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Open Trial of Tehran Mayor Begins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The open trial of Tehran Mayor
Gholamhussein Karbaschi, a moderate technocrat, on graft charges
opened on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The trial started at 09:00 local time (0430 GMT) at Tehran's
special judicial complex, which was surrounded by hundreds of riot
police equipped with sticks and arms.
</P>
<P>
It will last for days and Karbaschi is expected to give
explanations about the activities of the Tehran municipality in
the first session during the day.
</P>
<P>
Karbaschi was detained by the conservative judiciary on April 4
on charges of embezzlement, misappropriation of public funds and
mismanagement.
</P>
<P>
The supreme leader Ayatollah Ali Khamenei intervened, leading
to the release of the mayor after 11 days in custody.
</P>
<P>
The detention of Karbaschi triggered a conflict between the
conservatives and the moderates, who accuse the former of using
the case to undermine President Mohammad Khatami's government.
</P>
<P>
The conservatives attack the moderates for abusing freedom and
democracy advocated by Khatami and vow to punish those who violate
the laws.
</P>
<P>
About 150 people were present at the court while thousands of
others were permitted to watch the trial through closed circuit
television in a nearby hall.
</P>
<P>
Some 30 correspondents who received special permits were
allowed to enter the court, but many more, particularly foreign
nationals, were barred by court guards from entrancing.
</P>
<P>
People gathered in groups outside the court and debated with
each other over Karbaschi's case, saying that they expect the
mayor will be tried free from political struggle. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
