<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Shoe Export expected to decrease in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's shoe export is expected to
drop to an estimated 1.1 billion U.S. dollars, or 100 million
dollars less than the planned target, the Saigon Economic Times
said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
In the first five months this year, shoe export amounted to
more than 400 million dollars, up 11 percent over the same
period of last year, but lower than the planned growth target of 21
percent.
</P>
<P>
Shoe orders from South Korea dropped sharply due to the
monetary crisis in that country and orders from the European Union
and the U.S. Nike company are also decreasing, the weekly said.
</P>
</TEXT>
