<HEADLINE> Nigerian Army to Start Drug Producing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 7 (Xinhua) -- A drug factory with the capacity of
producing 760 million tablets and 80 million capsules a year will
be commissioned in Lagos next week by the Nigerian Army, the
Guardian newspaper reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The report said the factory, Nigerian Army Small Scale Drug
Manufacturing Unit, is a pioneering effort by the army to
guarantee the supply of genuine and quality drugs to the armed
forces, the police and the general public at affordable prices.
</P>
<P>
The factory is equipped with ultra modern producing unit as
well as state-of-art computerized analytical techniques and
equipment to achieve international good manufacturing practice,
the report said. 
