<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Investment Rising in Fuzhou Bonded Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, June 7 (Xinhua) -- A package of 37 projects involving
nearly 35 million US dollars of overseas investment have been
promised for the Fuzhou Bonded Zone in this capital of east
China's Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
The projects were signed at the 1998 Fujian International
Business Invitation Week.
</P>
<P>
Some 97 percent of the projects involve trade, and 92 percent
of the total are solely owned by overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
Opened five years ago, the bonded zone deals with comprehensive
businesses involved in international trade, export-oriented
processing, and goods storage and display.
</P>
<P>
By the end of May this year, the zone had more than 450
projects, involving nearly 500 million US dollars in total
investment, and had conducted 700 million US dollars-worth of
foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
Re-export from the zone now extends to Japan, the Republic of
Korea, and countries in Southeast Asia and South America.
</P>
<P>
The zone has become an important goods distribution center for
overseas-funded enterprises in east China's coastal areas.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980607.0110 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Work Starts On Hunan Section of Electrified Railway Line </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Construction work on a 637-km
electrified railway line in central China's Hunan Province is now
in full swing.
</P>
<P>
The line is one section of the electrified railway linking
Wuhan, capital of central China's Hubei Province, and Guangzhou,
capital of south China's Guangdong Province. Investment on the
section in Hunan will reach one billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The Wuhan-Guangzhou railway project will include bridges
totaling 4,159 m in length and other facilities, involving nearly
6.9 billion yuan in investment. 
</P>
