<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hebei's Private Science Firms Developing Rapidly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Private science and technology
enterprises have become an increasingly important driving force
for economic growth in north China's Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
Hebei now has 3,910 such enterprises, with total assets valued
at 27.64 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
These enterprises raked in gross profits worth more than 6.5
billion yuan from nearly 20 billion yuan in total business income
last year.
</P>
<P>
Wang Shikui, deputy chief of the provincial science and
technology commission, said that Hebei's private science and
technology firms have entered a period of sustained and rapid
growth.
</P>
<P>
Of the private science and technology enterprises in Hebei, 14
percent specialize in high technology. They have developed more
than 1,500 new products, with more than 130 of them considered
nationally or internationally advanced, he said.
</P>
<P>
Wang added that 601 of the enterprises have adopted the
shareholding or joint-stock systems to achieve economies of scale
and increase efficiency.
</P>
<P>
Some enterprises have actively participated in the national
effort to reform the country's state-owned enterprises through
mergers, contracting, leasing and takeovers, he said. 
</P>
