<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Rheumatism Treatment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Chinese doctors have helped in the
treatment of rheumatism and are becoming leaders in the field.
</P>
<P>
Doctors at Shanghai's Renji Hospital, led by a prominent
professor, Chen Shunle, who was just elected head of a medical
association for the study of rheumatism in the Asia-Pacific
region, have done research on systemic lupus erythematosus (SLE)
and are moving out in front in rheumatology.
</P>
<P>
The hospital has one of the most advanced medical labs in Asia
and specializes in immunobiology, immunopathology and molecular
biology. The research group has found that the incidence of SLE in
China is 0.07 percent and has successfully cultured an HEP-2 cell
strain for testing antinuclear antibodies, the doctors say.
</P>
<P>
They have also announced that the five-year and ten-year
survival rate of SLE patients is up to 98 percent and 84 percent
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Prof. Chen has also developed an effective way to diagnose
diseases of the human immune system by analysing a single drop of
blood.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
