<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Protecting The Ocean Around China's Southernmost Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, June 7 (Xinhua) -- A recent study by China's
Oceanography Bureau showed that 80 percent of the water around the
island province of Hainan is some of the best in China.
</P>
<P>
Hainan has only 34,000 square kilometers of land, but it
controls at least 2 million square kilometers of sea, or two
thirds of China's total.
</P>
<P>
The red tide that hit neighboring Guangdong Province and Hong
Kong recently did not bother Hainan and scientists say that the
ocean around Hainan has not deteriorated.
</P>
<P>
Since it became a province in 1988, Hainan has passed at least
20 regulations for protecting the ocean and 13 marine protection
zones have been set up.
</P>
<P>
Hainan put major industrial projects in the western part of the
province for pollution control and closed 75 enterprises with
severe pollution problems.
</P>
<P>
In the capital, Haikou, which has a population of 600,000, a
sewage treatment plant and equipment for industrial sewage
treatment have been built.
</P>
<P>
The maritime industry is expected to become a major industry
for Hainan because of its abundant marine resources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
