<P>
ROME, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Italian President Oscar Luigi Scalfaro
Saturday appealed to the leaders of Eritrea and Ethiopia to stop
all hostilities immediately.
</P>
<P>
In a written message to Eritrean President Isaias Afewerki and
Ethiopian President Negaso Gidada, Scalfaro said that Italy,
former colonial power of the two African countries, was
"profoundly disturbed by the recent tragic events" and was ready
to help them hold peace talks so that the road of mutual
understanding and collaboration could be found once again.
</P>
<P>
He said that Foreign Undersecretary Rino Serri, who would attend
an Organization for African Unity summit in Burkina Faso on
Monday, would meet with the two leaders to seek possible ways of
re-establishing peace.
</P>
<P>
He said when he visited Eritrea and Ethiopia last
November, he "heard talk of the feeling of brotherhood between
people of the two countries, of their close cooperation in all
fields, regional integration, peace and progress for the entire
horn of African region."
</P>
<P>
He was surprised by the fighting between the two nations, which
claimed innocent civilian lives, Scalfaro said.
</P>
<P>
Clashes between Ethiopia and Eritrea have been escalating for
weeks on a border dispute. Saturday morning, Ethiopian planes
bombed Asmara airport for the third time in two days and Eritrean
planes attacked the northern Ethiopian provincial capital of
Makalle, leaving dozens of people dead and over a hundred
injured. 
</P>
</TEXT>
