<HEADLINE> Two Earthquakes Jolt Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Two earthquakes hit Xanza County in
China's Tibet Autonomous Region yesterday evening, according to
the China Seismological Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The first quake, measuring 5.1 on the Richter Scale, occurred
at 19:06 p.m (Beijing time) and the second one measuring 5.3
occurred at 19:13 p.m. on June 6.
</P>
<P>
Xanza county is located northwest to Lhasa, capital of the
region.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the first quake was located at 30.5 degrees
north latitude and 89.5 degrees east longitude while that of the
second one was located at 30.5 degrees north latitude and 89
degrees east longitude, the bureau said.
</P>
<P>
So far there is no report of casualties from the quake-hit
area. 
