"China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- A Chinese trade expert urged the government to open up
foreign trade to private firms, adding the Asian financial crisis
has made it more urgent.
</P>
<P>
Qin Xuanren, deputy-secretary general of China Association of
International Trade, said a minimum 1.4 percent growth rate for
exports must be reached to ensure an eight percent of the annual
economy growth.
</P>
<P>
-- A sharp decrease in the profits of domestic airlines has
promoted the Civil Aviation Administration of China to impose
restrictions on air-fare discounts on domestic routes.
</P>
<P>
-- The U.S. government should ease restrictions on high-tech
exports to China if it wants to facilitate electronic commerce
between China and foreign countries, said Wang Jianguo, deputy
director of China International Electronic Commerce Center.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the move would also benefit U.S. foreign trade
firms, as China is its fourth biggest trade partner.  
</P>
