<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Calls on India, Pakistan to Solve Disputes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Regarding the issue of
Kashmir, India and Pakistan should look for a solution to their
disputes in accordance with the principles enshrined in relevant
U.N. resolutions and the Simla Agreement and through peaceful
negotiations, Qin Huasun, Chinese Ambassador to the United
Nations, said on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Ambassador Qin made the remarks at the Security Council meeting
which was held this morning to adopt a resolution concerning the
nuclear tests by India and Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
"The recent nuclear tests have also further strained the
bilateral relations between India and Pakistan, and undermined the
relative peace and stability in the Subcontinent," said the
Ambassador.
</P>
<P>
"What is worrisome is that the two countries have once again
entered into military engagement in Kashmir. There is no doubt
that escalation of the Kashmir dispute will further deteriorate
the situation, which will not only bring untold sufferings to the
two countries and their peoples, but inevitably endanger the peace
and stability in the region," he said.
</P>
<P>
"China calls upon India and Pakistan to be calm and
restrained, to restore talks between them, to halt any statements
or movements that may further escalate the tensions, and to
refrain from an arms race," Qin said.
</P>
<P>
"In Kashmir, they should respect and stick to the control
line, and they shall, under no circumstances, step across the
control line, or seek to change the state of affairs in the
region unilaterally," Qin stressed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
